---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Gigs — Turbulent Priest';
const description = 'A few engagements at a time, fussy about fit — for the problems that mutate while you look at them.';
const permalink = `${Astro.site.href}gigs`;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} permalink={permalink} current="gigs">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Bring me in</h1>

    <p>I take a few engagements at a time, and I'm fussy — not about grandeur, about <strong>fit.</strong></p>

    <p>What I'm <em>for</em> is the thing nobody in the room will say out loud: the contradiction buried in the brief, the AI roadmap confidently solving the wrong problem, the system that's about to surprise everyone who built it. I find the counter-example first — it's not a party trick, it's just how the wiring points. Put me in front of your plan and I'll show you where it's lying to you. I'll be kind about it. And I'll be right.</p>

    <p>If your problem has a clean answer in a textbook, hire someone faster and cheaper — genuinely, go. But if it's the kind that <strong>mutates while you look at it</strong> — where the philosophy isn't decoration <em>on</em> the work, it <em>is</em> the work — that's my water. I'll go a little further out than my feet can touch, because that's where the interesting problems live.</p>

    <p>The scannable version — dates, titles, the usual liturgy — is on LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/turbulentpriest/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/turbulentpriest</a>. But you're already looking at the real proof. It's the rest of this site.</p>

    <p>Come find me: <a class="gigs-contact" data-user="confession" data-domain="turbulentpriest.org" href="#"><span class="gigs-contact-addr">confession [at] turbulentpriest.org</span></a></p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Assemble the contact address at runtime so the raw string stays out of the static HTML (spam-harvest resistance).
  document.querySelectorAll('a.gigs-contact').forEach((node) => {
    const a = node as HTMLAnchorElement;
    const addr = `${a.dataset.user}@${a.dataset.domain}`;
    a.href = `mailto:${addr}`;
    const span = a.querySelector('.gigs-contact-addr');
    if (span) span.textContent = addr;
  });
</script>
